"cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY" 

This paper discusses a method for improving deep learning performance, specifically in text, speech, and image processing. It focuses on a technique called Dropout and proposes a more general model called the Stochastic Delta Rule (SDR) that outperforms Dropout on standard benchmarks. This paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with improving the performance of neural networks. It could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the use of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with image processing and feature discovery. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the use of a gradient-dependent simulated annealing method.
